quote: When they go low, we go high.
author: Michelle Obama

quote: I raise up my voice—not so that I can shout, but so that those without a voice can be heard. We cannot all succeed when half of us are held back.
author: Malala Yousafzai

quote: We may encounter many defeats, but we must not be defeated.
author: Maya Angelou

quote: I have learned over the years that when one's mind is made up, this diminishes fears; knowing what must be done does away with fear.
author: Rosa Parks

quote: I'd rather regret the things I’ve done than regret the things I haven’t done.
author: Lucille Ball

quote: If you don’t like the road you’re walking, start paving another one.
author: Dolly Parton

quote: Find something you're passionate about and keep tremendously interested in it.
author: Julia Child

quote: So often in life, things that you regard as an impediment turn out to be great, good fortune.
author: Ruth Bader Ginsburg

quote: Normal is not something to aspire to, it’s something to get away from.
author: Jodie Foster

quote: I don't go by the rule book. I lead from the heart, not the head.
author: Princess Diana
